ofile?language=EN>DemonMage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/02 1:01:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10302.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> New Testserver Stuff</span><hr size=1> This is copied from Casters Realm since I'm too lazy to put my own spin on it, and they do a good job =-p<br><br><br>More from Test Server:<br><br>"We've added some new functionality for the messages generated when you hit something or when something hits you. Here's the programmer version of the instructions. We'll get more user friendly instructions in to the manual supplement by the time we patch the live servers. <br><br>Added /hitsmode, this lets you control how you see the messages for when you hit something. This allows you to have information about others' hits and misses and your own hits and misses to a location outside your chat window. As we are still working on this, please use the in-game help for more information (it will be updated as changes are made). You can access the in-game help for this new feature by typing /hitsmode "<br><br>Unsure what this means?  Basically it means you will no longer have to have your chat window spammed by combat messages, you can make these go outside your chat window.  You can have one for your hits and another one for other peoples hits. <br><br>This will be a really nice improvement to the game UI once it goes live.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umiriameleprester.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MiriamelePrester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/02 5:08:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10302.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Testserver Stuff</span><hr size=1> You can also have an area for damage you take... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxitix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xitix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/02 5:54:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10302.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Testserver Stuff</span><hr size=1> Odd way for them to implement it. I allways thought they would just add more settings to each filter. For example Other's hits : MAIN 2nd 3rd Off, where the messages would go to the main chat window, a 2nd chat window, a 3rd chat window or be filtered. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udenuvien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Denuvien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/02 9:33:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10302.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Testserver Stuff</span><hr size=1> well they say the implimentation is half-assed right now, so maybe we'll see something simpler like that when it finally goes live. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqualm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qualm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/02 10:52:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10302.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Maybe ...</span><hr size=1> Maybe they will add &quot;floaty numbers&quot; to the interface like the nifty old method in Microprose Darklands, where the damage number drifted off above the toons heads like smoke signals ... they provided great feedback on the damage-over-time stream.<br><br>Qualm, Barbarian Shaman, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubronusblackblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bronus Blackblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/02 11:18:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10302.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maybe ...</span><hr size=1> Separate windows...DAoC ripoff, hehe.  Separate windows isn't a bad idea if implemented right, that was you can still log the damage withouth having to spam your chat window. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utabbran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tabbran</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/02 11:57:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10302.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maybe ...</span><hr size=1> There's been unique input windows for various messages received since way before DAOC :P<br><br>I played on a MUD that required a special client because of the windows where the combat, chat, etc messages all went, hardly unique to DAOC :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubronusblackblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bronus Blackblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/02 12:15:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10302.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maybe ...</span><hr size=1> True, I should point out that they have only recently implemented this since their only competition (DAoC) has come out.  Not that DAoC was the pioneer, but I doubt EQ got the idea directly from a MUD.  Most of EQ is MUD-based, true, but why didn't they have this in at the beginning of EQ then?<br><br>I guess my point is that EQ would be foolish not to look at the strong points of their competition, I doubt they are going back to look at MUDs at this point. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxitix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xitix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0